// kolm public seed dataset: email-classifier
// status: synthetic, public domain, illustrative only
// purpose: starter examples for routing inbound email into a small label set.
//          labels: billing, support, sales, spam, account, feedback, other.
//          modeled after common helpdesk triage taxonomies (no real messages).
// usage:   bootstrap with `kolm seeds bootstrap --task email-classifier`, then
//          REPLACE these with your own real examples before training. K-score
//          measured on synthetic data is not K-score measured on your data.
// license: public domain (CC0). these rows do not describe any real person.
{"input": "Subject: Double charge on my invoice\n\nI was billed twice for the October plan. Can you refund the duplicate charge?", "output": {"label": "billing"}, "tags": ["billing", "refund"]}
